body: I don't get this issue on the console or notebooks, btw. Will see what I can do for atom.
Don't really get this issue on atom either... Is there a setting I need to switch?
Ah, atom is not showing me kernel suggestions. How do I turn that on?
Well if you have my `language-stata` package installed, when you open up a do file, it sets the bracket-matcher to automatically enter a `'`. Do you have that package installed?
The tick does match. What I am not seeing is autocomplete (and I do have that enabled).
It seems that it doesn't show me any globals or locals in the completions, but it will show me variables, scalars, and matrices. Not sure what's up with that...
oh do it outside of a string.
Yes. Trying it outside a string.
Hydrogen currently is hard-coded to not autocomplete inside strings. I submitted a PR  https://github.com/nteract/hydrogen/issues/1383

Not trying inside a string. Just not getting any suggestions.

![error_local_completions_atom](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4219197/44378769-d2b48980-a4d0-11e8-9776-e42036236db2.png)
So, I can't debug because I can't reproduce. So what I could do is just not close the suggestion. Will be a bit of work but not too much (I'd have to turn it off for ${} and `=scalar()` as well).
Weird. None of those suggestions are coming from Hydrogen/the kernel. They're all coming from language-stata / other text in the editor.

This is getting annoying for me. To my mind, the autocompletion should be separate from the bracket completion. I'd be surprised if there weren't a plugin for Jupyter qtconsole to do bracket (and quote) completions.
Sure; will remove. It's not too hard to take out.
